BHP Billiton, Metorex, Vodacom: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-04-11T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-10/bhp-billiton-metorex-vodacom-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose 173.02,
or 0.5 percent, to 32,806.27 in Johannesburg.  BHP Billiton Plc (BIL)  : The world’s largest mining
company is in talks to buy Royal Dutch Shell Plc’s stake in
Woodside Petroleum Ltd. and make a full takeover offer worth
A$46 billion ($48.6 billion) for  Australia ’s second-biggest oil
and gas producer. The stock price climbed 5.60 rand, or 2
percent, to 280.70 rand, the highest closing price since Feb.
17.  Metorex Ltd. (MTX)  : The copper producer may be bought
over by Vale SA, the world’s second-biggest miner, for 7.5
billion rand ($1.1 billion), or 7.35 rand a share. The stock
price dropped 5 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 7.05 rand after
reaching its highest level since October 2008 earlier.  Vodacom Group Ltd. (VOD)  : South Africa’s largest
provider of mobile-phone services was ordered by a judge in
Kinshasa to put shares worth $40.8 million in escrow. The
company is being sued by a former consultant who helped the
company with negotiations during a dispute with its business
partner in the Democratic Republic of Congo. The stock fell 68
cents, or 0.9 percent, to 78.32 rand.  The following shares begin trading without the rights to
their latest dividends:
       Aeci Ltd. (AFE)  , Beige Holdings (BEG SJ), Capital &
Counties Properties Plc (CCO SJ), Ceramic Industries Ltd. (CRM
SJ), Group Five Ltd. (GRF SJ), Howden Africa Holdings Ltd. (HWN
SJ), Iliad Africa Ltd. (ILA SJ), Marshall Monteagle Plc (MMP
SJ), Metair Investments Ltd. (MTA SJ),  Mondi Ltd. (MND)  ,
 Mondi Plc (MNP)  ,  Murray & Roberts Holdings Ltd. (MUR)  , Old
Mutual Plc (OML SJ), Tradehold Ltd. (TDH SJ), Wilson Bayly
Holmes-Ovcon Ltd. (WBO SJ).  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY)   increased 3 percent to
$27.10.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU)   climbed 3.2 percent to
$51.09.  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)   rose 2.3 percent to $84.52.
 DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY)   fell 1.3 percent to $5.46.  Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI)   gained 2.2 percent to $18.55. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) rose 1.5 percent to $15.56. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) increased 0.2 percent to $29.75.  Sappi Ltd. (SPP) 
 slipped 0.9 percent to $5.40.  Sasol Ltd. (SSL)  
climbed 0.7 percent to $60.05.  To contact the reporter on this story:
